The paper presents an automated tool for software testing, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The tool is capable of testing both traditional software and AI applications, indicating a potential overlap with the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also mentions the use of test case metrics and filters, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the tool can be used for test set optimization, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper focuses on datamorphism combination strategies, which are specific to software testing and therefore reinforce the likelihood of the paper belonging to the software engineering category.
